Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat the @butter{20%g} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once melted, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While the onions cook, pour the @water{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with
a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil.
Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to
serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Zest and quarter the @lime{1/2}.

Once the onion is cooked, add the @ginger puree{15%g}, garlic and
@ground turmeric{1%sachet}. Stir well and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the tomatoes, @coconut milk{180%ml}, @water{100%ml} and
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to
medium.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened and the tomatoes have cooked down,
stirring occasionally, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Drain the @fish pie mix{1%pack} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, gently stir through the fish pie mix.

Lower the heat and simmer gently, stirring occasionally, until the fish is
cooked, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the centre.

Add a squeeze of lime juice, then taste and add more salt, pepper and lime
juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Share between
bowls and top with your moqueca.

Sprinkle over the @chilli flakes{1%pinch} and serve with any remaining lime
wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!